{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In this framework, a single-time extraction of knowledge was performed in response to the user's initial query.",
    "Various methods were conceived to incorporate this external knowledge retrieval.",
    "For instance, Guu et al. [5] introduced a language model that incorporated latent knowledge retrieval during pretraining, whereas Ram et al.",
    "[26] chose to keep the core LM architecture untouched, simply appending grounding documents to its input.",
    "Meanwhile, Shi et al. [30] perceived the language model as an inscrutable entity, complementing it with an externally trainable retrieval module."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For instance, Guu et al. [5] introduced a language model that incorporated latent knowledge retrieval during pretraining, whereas Ram et al.",
    "[26] chose to keep the core LM architecture untouched, simply appending grounding documents to its input.",
    "Meanwhile, Shi et al. [30] perceived the language model as an inscrutable entity, complementing it with an externally trainable retrieval module."
  ]
}